~ shared/schema.wit — templates and headings reused across the thesis.
~ Single-line inline defs with named captures cover the common cases.

~ Inline citation: @cite |author Weil| |year 1952| produces "Weil (1952)".
#cite: ::author:: (::year::) !!

~ Inline citation with page: "Weil (1952, p. 42)".
#citepage: ::author:: (::year::, p. ::page::) !!

~ Inline theorem-style emphasis: "Theorem 1 — The Asymmetry of Looking".
#theorem: **Theorem ::number::** — ::statement:: !!

~ Block chapter header. Lays down ATX markdown that reads as a heading
~ in markdown and as plain prose in HTML — both outputs stay legible.
#chapter ||number, title||
# Chapter ::number::: ::title::
chapter#

~ Block section header.
#section ||title||
## ::title::
section#

~ Subsection header.
#subsection ||title||
### ::title::
subsection#

~ Inline draft watermark — referenced from a conditional in master.wit.
#watermark: _Draft — not for distribution._ !!

~ Wrapper for a bibliography entry. Lets +#bibliography partials each
~ produce one renderable block instead of fragmenting into many text
~ paragraphs when the inline def expands.
#entry: ... !!
